args: With everyone's help, the prince and Lea begin\ntracking down all the copies of the ebon fiend\nthat were assigned to the imperial army.
These copies we are dealing with\nsound formidable indeed.
Which is why we must move against them\nbefore they can do further harm.
I think Ranzal should be back from\ngathering information soon.
Bad news, guysâ€”all them ebon fiend\ncopies up'n ran off from the army!
Sounds like they're all headin'\nfor the same place, too...
The village where Lea's pops died.
Whatever could have attracted\nall these fiends to this place?
This is where the original ebon fiend got\ntaken down, yeah? Maybe they've all\ncome back what to settle the score.
Then it falls to me to serve as their\nopponent in my father's stead.
Don't get too far ahead of us, Lea.
I shall not make the same error\na second time, Your Highness.
Then let's work together to take\nthese things down for good!
That was a most difficult battle.
Still, all of the villagers are unharmed,\nwhich is the best we could have hoped for.
Indeed, I was able to protect the same\ntownâ€”and peopleâ€”as my father.
Say, are you the daughter of the knight\nwho defended this village ten years ago?
If not, she fights with the exact same style!\nI remember it from when I was a kid.
Of course! He saved our lives!
We are a poor, simple village, and yet he\ndidn't hesitate to give his life for ours.
We'd all be worm's food if not for him.
Then his deeds live on in the hearts\nof all the people here...
There shoulda been more fiends than this.
Ugh. Well, I guess we know\nwhere the other fiends are.
You cannot be thinking to fight them;\nwe're barely standing as it is!
Eh, we can do it. Hell, at least this group\nain't as big as the last one.
I will fight until the last of these fiends\nare dispatched. However, all villagers\nmust flee this place at once!
Just as my father before me, I swear\nyou shall not come to harm. Now go!
(Is this how I meet my end? Unable to\nprotect what's important to me?)
I don't know who threw that stone,\nbut this is my chance! Haaaah!
*cough* Nothing bruised save my ego.\nBut who threw that stone?
It's the villagers! ...And a lot of farm tools?
Why did you not flee as we bade you?!
Fighting fiends is scary, but we'll do it\nif it means protecting what's ours!
We'll never again stand by as someone\nfights and dies for our sake!
Bwa ha ha! They got them fiends\nshakin' in their boots!\n...Or, uh, whatever fiends wear.
The sound of their battle cry\nfills me anew with energy!
They're filled with the courage\nto protect what they care about.
THIS is your father's legacy, Lea!
Then I shall be equally courageous!
We split our forces here, people!\nAll who can handle close combat,\nfollow me and the prince!
Everyone else should support us\nfrom behind with stones!
This shall be our final battle. Move out!
That should be the last of them for true.
Yep. Looks like we won the day.
We did it! We did it!
And yet, the village itself is in ruins.
Looks like we're going to have company\nat the Halidom while they rebuild.
If that's the case, will you teach us how\nto fight in the meantime, ma'am?
Why would you ask this of me?
We want to help youâ€”not just\nrely on you for protection.

Maybe just start by teachin' some basic
self-defense, yeah? Then ya can pull out
the ones what got talent and give 'em
more advanced instruction.
Hell, they had the fiends wettin'\nthemselves earlierâ€”might be ya\nfind a real warrior or three here.
Your father planted the seeds of this\ncourage, Lea, but that isn't enough.
They need skills and knowledge, too.
So maybe it's time to pick up where\nyour father left off and teach them.
Very well. But I hope you are prepared,\nfor I will be a strict teacher!
